to add a new library file to the current project
create a new folder: lib to keep all external jar files (for convenience)
File>Project Structure>Libraries> +
find the jar in the lib folder and select it, apply and close

or File>Project Structure>Module>Dependencies> '+' >
   >find the JAR in the correct project/lib folder
   > select the JAR file, click apply



*********
in Eclipse
do the same thing to add jar to the library

also add TestNG plugin in the Eclipse
Eclipse> Help> Eclipse Marketplace > search plugin "TestNG" > install it
Restart Eclipse